e on the Currying concept. Will you actually use it a lot in real life? Honestly, it depends — Currying is one of those techniques that varies a lot from team to team. The first time you stare at ",[60,1013,1014],{},"const curryAdd = (a) => (b) => (c) => a + b + c;"," you do get a bit of a WTF moment, but once you break it apart you'll see it's really just a simple closure.",[12,1017,1018,1019,525,1025,1030],{},"One last thing worth mentioning: some libraries use Currying under the hood, like ",[82,1020,1024],{"href":1021,"rel":1022},"https:\u002F\u002Framdajs.com\u002F",[1023],"nofollow","Ramda",[82,1026,1029],{"href":1027,"rel":1028},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Flodash\u002Flodash\u002Fwiki\u002FFP-Guide",[1023],"lodash\u002Ffp",". If you're curious, it's worth taking a look at how those libraries do it.",[12,1032,1033],{},"That's a wrap for this one. Hope it gives you a decent first feel for Currying, and that you'll give it a shot when the right moment comes along.",[1035,1036,1037],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sOudu, html code.shiki .sOudu{--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-default:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .scAaK, html code.shiki .scAaK{--shiki-light:#6F42C1;--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .s8XSl, html code.shiki .s8XSl{--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-default:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .syBk-, html code.shiki .syBk-{--shiki-light:#E36209;--shiki-default:#E36209;--shiki-dark:#FFB757}html .light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html.light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);backgr